  "notes": "Manual capture from the official Journal of Neurotrauma instructions supplied on April 12, 2026. This journal explicitly considers original research, reviews, short communications, and letters to the editor; case reports are not accepted. It accepts format-neutral first submissions but still requires IRB/disclosure elements and a 500-word Transparency, Rigor, and Reproducibility Summary after the conclusion. Operational fit rule: mechanistic biomarker and pathophysiological studies can remain bounded in translational maturity if claims are explicitly limited and the evidence chain, declarations, and reproducibility summary are complete. Additional useful but non-blocking follow-up would be the linked article-type-specific rigor pages for pathophysiological mechanistic studies and fluid biomarker papers."
